Play more. You can climb out of it but you only have like 70 games of ranked.  Also.
 PLAY SOLO. Solo games are easier. The duo system matches you either with being of supposedly less skill or against people of more skill. However you wanna look at it, that's how it compensates for duos. 
{{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}}

**Practice CS**

Go into the Practice Tool and work on last-hitting minions. Do this until you can get 100 CS in 13 minutes. 

**Play Simple Champions**

Pick 2 roles you want to play. Pick 2 simple champions for each role, and a spare Support champion. Play them in EVERY game. Here's a small guide:

Top Lane: {{champion:75}} {{champion:58}} 

Jungle: {{champion:19}} {{champion:57}} 

Mid: {{champion:1}} {{champion:99}} 

ADC: {{champion:21}} {{champion:15}} 

Support: {{champion:37}} {{champion:89}} 

**Constantly Check Your Mini-Map**

Ganks suck. They're the soul reason for my tilt. Check your mini-map frequently to see where the enemies are. If you don't know where the Jungler, nearby solo-laner, or Support are, then don't try and fight.
